article.headline: Creighton 67, Drake 62
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Nate Funk scored 21 points and Dane Watts added 16 to lead Creighton past Drake 67-62 Saturday. Creighton (16-7, 10-3 MVC) picked up its fifth straight win over Drake (12-12, 3-10) and its fourth straight victory overall. Drake's Nick Grant tied the game at 62 with 1:42 left. Funk, who shot 7-of-13 from the field, sank a 17-foot jumper to push Creighton back ahead by two. Josh Young was then called for charging, giving the ball back to the Bluejays. Nick Porter made one of two free throws and Funk added a pair from the line to seal the win. Pierce Hibma hit four 3-pointers for Creighton in the second half, including three straight in under two minutes. Ajay Calvin led the Bulldogs with 19 points. Young added 12 for Drake, which led 32-30 at halftime.
